#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.104"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.104:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:0.2"
msgid "11. Yogakkhemivagga"
msgstr "11. Sanctuary"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.104:0.3"
msgid "104. Yogakkhemisutta"
msgstr "104. Sanctuary"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.85"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.2"
msgid "“Yogakkhemipariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you an exposition of the teaching, an explanation "
"of one who has reached sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, yogakkhemipariyāyo dhammapariyāyo?"
msgstr ""
"And what is an exposition of the teaching, an explanation of one who has "
"reached sanctuary?"

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.5"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.6"
msgid ""
"Te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ "
"anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them "
"like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the "
"future."

# See BB’s notes on the pun involved here. I don’t attempt to retain the pun.
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.7"
msgid ""
"Tesañca pahānāya akkhāsi yogaṃ, tasmā tathāgato ‘yogakkhemī’ti vuccati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"He teaches meditation for giving them up. That’s why the Realized One is "
"called one who has reached sanctuary. …"

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.8"
msgid ""
"santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.9"
msgid ""
"Te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ "
"anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them "
"like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the "
"future."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.10"
msgid "Tesañca pahānāya akkhāsi yogaṃ, tasmā tathāgato ‘yogakkhemī’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"He teaches meditation for giving them up. That’s why the Realized One is "
"called one who has reached sanctuary."

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yogakkhemipariyāyo dhammapariyāyo”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is an exposition of the teaching, an explanation of one who has reached "
"sanctuary.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.12"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
